# Agent rules for vantage-ui-examples

Concise guidelines for working in this repo. (A fuller agent skill will come
later; see todo/agent-skill.md.)

## What this repo is
A public, **black-box** example catalog + BDD UI test suite for the
closed-source `vantage-ui` app.
- The ONLY way to control the app is its MCP API. Never link or vendor
  vantage-ui source code. Do NOT add gpui or `TestAppContext` here — those are
  vantage-ui's in-process tools and cannot drive the published binary.
- Tests launch the real published binary (path from `$VANTAGE_UI_BIN`) and
  drive it over MCP (`http://127.0.0.1:14488/mcp`). Today the app exposes only
  the `list_logs` tool; richer interaction is blocked on new MCP tools (see
  todo/scenario-features.md).

## Layout contract
- `test-framework/` — the reusable engine (`src/{world,launcher,mcp_client}.rs`,
  in the lib) plus the `vantage-ui-test` driver binary and the shared steps
  (`src/steps/`, in the binary). Shared `*.feature` live in
  `test-framework/features/common/`.
- `apps/<name>/` — one self-contained example app: `inventory/` (the YAML
  catalog), `tests/` (app-specific `*.feature`), `README.md`, optional `docs/`.
- Shared steps and common features live in the framework — never copy them per
  app.

## Adding an app
1. Create `apps/<name>/inventory/` with `datasource/ table/ page/ menu/` YAML.
2. Keep it **offline-clean**: launching must log no ERROR. Prefer a CSV
   datasource (it opens no connection at startup) or a committed, seeded SQLite
   file. A datasource pointing at an unreachable DB logs an ERROR and fails the
   startup test.
3. Add a `README.md`. The shared startup check runs automatically; add
   `tests/*.feature` only for app-specific behavior.

## Adding a scenario
- Reuse existing steps; add a new step only when none fits. Keep gherkin
  declarative — put logic in step functions, not the feature text.
- Tag not-yet-runnable scenarios `@wip`; the driver filters them out.

## Running & quality
- `cargo run -p test-framework -- apps/<name>` (single) or `-- --all`.
- Set `$VANTAGE_UI_BIN`, or build `../vantage-ui` with `cargo build --release`.
- Keep `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy` clean.
- Pin `rmcp` to the exact version vantage-ui's server uses (wire compat).
- Don't depend on wall-clock timing — poll the MCP logs for readiness.

## Scope discipline
Capture out-of-scope-but-needed work in `todo/*.md`; don't silently expand
scope or park unscoped work in code comments.
